.TH CMUX-OPEN 1 "2026-07-21" "HEARTH" "HEARTH cmux integration"
.SH NAME
cmux-open \- launch a cmux workspace in the open (non-confidential) tier
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B cmux-open
.RB [ --check ]
.RB [ --dry-run ]
.RI [ REPO ]
.br
.B cmux-open --cost
.SH DESCRIPTION
The counterpart to
.BR cmux-sealed (1).
The
.B open
tier permits what the sealed tier forbids: cloud VMs, networked Docker, and frontier escalation.
Because that is real egress,
.B cmux-open
opens the tier
.B only
for a repo explicitly classified
.B open
(ADR\-C003,
.BR config/cmux/tiers.yaml )
and
.B fails closed to sealed
for any confidential or unclassified repo. The default is sealed; the open tier is strictly opt\-in.
.PP
If
.I REPO
is omitted it defaults to the current directory. Every open decision is written to an audit log.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --check
Verify eligibility only; do not launch. A grant is not logged (a refusal always is).
.TP
.B --dry-run
Verify, log the grant, and print the launch command, but do not launch.
.TP
.B --cost
Show the HEARTH escalation/cost rollup for open\-tier frontier use. (Frontier spend from a pane's own
agent is outside HEARTH's meter.)
.SH "EXIT STATUS"
.TP
.B 0
Eligible for the open tier (or --cost/--check succeeded).
.TP
.B 2
Refused \(em the repo is sealed or unclassified; fail\-closed.
.TP
.B 64
Usage error.
.SH FILES
.TP
.B config/cmux/tiers.yaml
Tier policy. A repo is open only via an explicit
.B open:
rule and no matching
.BR sealed_override .
.TP
.B $CMUX_TIER_AUDIT_LOG
Append\-only audit log of open\-tier grants and refusals (default
.BR ~/.hearth/cmux-tier-audit.log ).
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR cmux-sealed (1),
.B docs/cmux/RUNBOOK_open.md ,
.B docs/cmux/ARCHITECTURE.md ,
.B docs/cmux/DECISIONS.md
.SH CAVEAT
Never open a confidential repo here. The gate enforces this from
.BR tiers.yaml ,
but a mis\-written broad
.B open:
rule is dangerous \(em keep a
.B sealed_override
for every confidential marker.
